</p>

<p>
This supports the use of predictive modeling because the feature space includes multiple workforce dimensions instead of a small set of overpowering predictors.
</p>

<p>
The correlation results also reinforce the need for later model evaluation: workforce outcomes are shaped by interacting patterns across compensation, tenure, wellbeing, engagement, monitoring, and privacy-related variables.
</p>

</div>
